  "texts": [
    "Large online platforms serving significant user bases must also conduct risk assessments and external audits (Articles [26][27].",
    "Ps shoulder more extensive due diligence requirements, including granting vetted researchers access to platform data to monitor risks (Article 40).",
    "Their compliance systems and risk mitigation measures must undergo mandatory independent auditing (Articles [35][36][37].VLOP policies should be vetted by external experts to identify inconsistencies with DSA obligations (Recital 105).",
    "However, critics argue these duties may still be excessive for smaller platforms.",
    "Overall, intermediaries must implement reasonable duties of care, proportional to their resources and risks posed to society based on factors like user base size, reach, impact and capabilities (Recital 40).Independent auditing mechanisms (Articles 37) To facilitate enhanced accountability of very large intermediaries, the DSA contains extensive provisions concerning independent external audits of platform activities with potential societal impacts."
  ]
